The paper describes an empirical study of the usage of a mobility self-tracking app, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study also involves the analysis of user interactions and questionnaire responses, which could be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), systems and control (cs.SD), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
